Project 1 - Description: You'll develop and benchmark a modular computer vision pipeline that combines custom object detectors (YOLO and others), modern segmentation models (SAM3), and multi-LLM orchestration (Gemini / OpenAI) to improve robustness in real-world conditions. Early-stage work includes comparative testing of segmentation architectures—U-Net, DeepLab, attention U-Nets—especially for fine-grained defects like hairline cracks that are easy to miss. You'll iterate rapidly, evaluate performance metrics, and refine model pipelines based on live feedback from annotation teams.
Project 2 - Description: You'll design and build an annotation workflow integrated with CVAT, enabling expert reviewers to label defect type, severity, geometry, confidence, and review status efficiently. The system will incorporate model and LLM suggestions to accelerate labelling and maintain consistency, with optional scalability via Amazon Mechanical Turk. High-quality annotations feed directly back into training pipelines—creating a tight feedback loop that continuously improves model performance.

Project 1 - Title: Building AI models for detection of deepfake images
Project 1 - Description: Truuth specialises in the detection of deepfake content.  This requires us to continually monitor the State-of-the-Art in ML models for the detection of deepfakes.  We build new models and retrain existing deep learning models every month.  Applicants should have some experience training ML models.
Project 2 - Description: In addition to deepfake detection, we also build models to detect a wide range of image and document falsification scenarios.  This project is focused on reviewing fraudulent images and documents supplied by our clients and designing new solutions for detecting the forgery.  Applicants should have experience with data science and creativity to replicate fraudster behaviour and design new checks to detect the fraud.
Project 3 - Title: Detection of adverse media and compliance with AML/CTF
Project 3 - Description: This project is focused on building a solution that can monitor social media to determine if there are potential risks associated with a particular person or entity.  In addition to social media we need to perform regular updates for Politically Exposed Persons and Sanctions.  Applicants should have experience in integration of 3rd party APIs.
